91
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:36,200
... when Hobbits will shape the fortunes of all.

92
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:42,499
The 22nd day of September...

93
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:46,399
...in the year 1400...

94
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:48,809
...by Shire-reckoning.

95
00:07:48,810 --> 00:07:54,809
Bag End, Bagshot Row.
Hobbiton, Westfarthing...

96
00:07:54,810 --> 00:07:57,009
...the Shire...

97
00:07:57,010 --> 00:08:01,210
...Middle-earth.

98
00:08:04,410 --> 00:08:09,110
The third age of this world.

99
00:08:10,010 --> 00:08:16,510


100
00:08:19,410 --> 00:08:23,410
There and back again.

101
00:08:23,910 --> 00:08:25,909
A Hobbit's tale.

102
00:08:25,910 --> 00:08:31,210
By Bilbo Baggins.

103
00:08:34,610 --> 00:08:37,109
Now...

104
00:08:37,110 --> 00:08:40,409
...where to begin?

105
00:08:40,410 --> 00:08:42,910
Ah, yes....

106
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:48,909
"Concerning...

107
00:08:48,910 --> 00:08:51,609
...Hobbits."

108
00:08:51,610 --> 00:08:55,309
Hobbits have been living and farming
in the four Farthings of the Shire...

109
00:08:55,310 --> 00:08:57,519
...for many hundreds of years...

110
00:08:57,520 --> 00:09:00,719
...quite content to ignore and be ignored...

111
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:04,219
...by the world of the big folk.

112
00:09:04,220 --> 00:09:10,019
Middle-earth being, after all,
full of strange creatures beyond count...

113
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:13,419
...Hobbits must seem of little importance...

114
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:17,619
...being neither renowned as great warriors...

115
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:23,120
...nor counted among the very wise.

116
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:30,319
Frodo! Someone at the door.

117
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:33,119
In fact, it has been remarked by some...

118
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:37,919
... that Hobbits' only real passion is for food.

119
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:40,319
A rather unfair observation...

120
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:44,419
...as we have also developed a keen
interest in the brewing of ales...

121
00:09:44,420 --> 00:09:47,619
...and the smoking of pipe-weed.

122
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:50,619
But where our hearts truly lie...

123
00:09:50,620 --> 00:09:53,519
...is in peace and quiet...

124
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,819
...and good, tilled earth.

125
00:09:55,820 --> 00:10:02,320
For all Hobbits share a love of things that grow.

126
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:08,719
And yes, no doubt to others our ways seem quaint.

127
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:14,519
But today of all days.
It is brought home to me...

128
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:21,720
It is no bad thing to celebrate a simple life.

129
00:10:24,630 --> 00:10:29,230
Frodo, the door!

130
00:10:31,630 --> 00:10:33,729
Sticklebacks. Where is that boy?

131
00:10:33,730 --> 00:10:36,930
Frodo!

132
