925
01:26:29,430 --> 01:26:32,029
We were that worried about you.
Weren't we, Mr. Gandalf?

926
01:26:32,030 --> 01:26:38,430
By the skills of Lord Elrond,
you're beginning to mend.

927
01:26:38,530 --> 01:26:43,530
Welcome to Rivendell, Frodo Baggins.

928
01:26:44,250 --> 01:27:03,750
<i><font color="#008000">♫ A, Elbereth Gilthoniel</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(O, Elbereth Kindler of Stars)</font></i>

929
01:27:04,250 --> 01:27:18,750
<i><font color="#008000">♫ silivren penna míriel</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Glittering light falling like shining jewels)</font></i>

930
01:27:19,250 --> 01:27:25,750
<i><font color="#008000">♫ A El'</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(O, the Stars)</font></i>

931
01:27:30,220 --> 01:27:33,719
- Bilbo!
- Hello, Frodo, my lad.

932
01:27:33,720 --> 01:27:36,920
Bilbo.

933
01:27:40,320 --> 01:27:42,319
There and back again

934
01:27:42,320 --> 01:27:46,520
A hobbit's Tale, by Bilbo Baggins.''

935
01:27:48,220 --> 01:27:52,019
- This is wonderful.
- I meant to go back...

936
01:27:52,020 --> 01:27:56,319
...wonder at the powers of Mirkwood...

937
01:27:56,320 --> 01:27:58,819
...visit Lake-town...

938
01:27:58,820 --> 01:28:02,819
...see the Lonely Mountain again.

939
01:28:02,820 --> 01:28:08,920
But age, it seems, has finally caught up with me.

940
01:28:19,820 --> 01:28:22,019
I miss the Shire.

941
01:28:22,020 --> 01:28:27,419
I spent all my childhood pretending
I was off somewhere else.

942
01:28:27,420 --> 01:28:32,320
Off with you, on one of your adventures.

943
01:28:33,820 --> 01:28:38,820
But my own adventure turned out
to be quite different.

944
01:28:42,820 --> 01:28:47,219
I'm not like you, Bilbo.

945
01:28:47,220 --> 01:28:50,820
My dear boy.

946
01:28:53,620 --> 01:28:54,819
Now, what have I forgotten?


947
01:28:55,250 --> 01:29:02,750
<i><font color="#008000">♫ A, Elbereth Gil[thoniel]</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(O, Elbereth Kindler of Stars)</font></i>

948
01:28:55,320 --> 01:28:58,219
Packed already?

949
01:28:58,220 --> 01:29:00,219
No harm in being prepared.

950
01:29:00,220 --> 01:29:03,019
- I thought you wanted to see the elves.
- I do.

951
01:29:03,020 --> 01:29:06,119
- More than anything.
- I did.

952
01:29:06,120 --> 01:29:08,819
It's just....

953
01:29:08,820 --> 01:29:11,619
We did what Gandalf wanted, didn't we?

954
01:29:11,620 --> 01:29:15,619
We got the ring this far, to Rivendell.
And I thought...

955
01:29:15,620 --> 01:29:19,019
...seeing as how you're on the mend,
we'd be off soon.

956
01:29:19,020 --> 01:29:22,120
Off home.

957
01:29:24,820 --> 01:29:28,220
You are right, Sam.

958
01:29:29,020 --> 01:29:32,319
We did what we set out to do.

959
01:29:32,320 --> 01:29:36,320
The ring will be safe in Rivendell.

960
01:29:39,020 --> 01:29:42,119
I am ready to go home.

961
01:29:42,120 --> 01:29:44,319
His strength returns.

962
01:29:44,320 --> 01:29:50,719
That wound will never fully heal.
He will carry it the rest of his life.

963
01:29:50,720 --> 01:29:53,319
And yet to have come so far still bearing the ring...

964
01:29:53,320 --> 01:29:57,309
...the Hobbit has shown extraordinary
resilience to its evil.

965
01:29:57,310 --> 01:30:00,919
It is a burden he should never have had to bear.

966
01:30:00,920 --> 01:30:06,439
- We can ask no more of Frodo.
- Gandalf, the enemy is moving.

967
01:30:06,440 --> 01:30:11,339
Sauron's forces are massing in the East.
His eye is fixed on Rivendell.

968
01:30:11,340 --> 01:30:14,339
And Saruman, you tell me, has betrayed us.

969
01:30:14,340 --> 01:30:18,239
Our list of allies grows thin.

970
01:30:18,240 --> 01:30:21,239
His treachery runs deeper than you know.

971
01:30:21,240 --> 01:30:25,139
By foul craft, Saruman
has crossed orcs with goblin-men.

972
01:30:25,140 --> 01:30:27,839
He's breeding an army in the caverns of Isengard.

973
01:30:27,840 --> 01:30:32,649
An army that can move in sunlight
and cover great distance at speed.

974
01:30:32,650 --> 01:30:35,449
Saruman is coming for the ring.

975
01:30:35,450 --> 01:30:39,749
This evil cannot be concealed
by the power of the elves.

976
01:30:39,750 --> 01:30:45,450
We do not have the strength to
fight both Mordor and Isengard!

977
01:30:47,960 --> 01:30:50,359
Gandalf...

978
01:30:50,360 --> 01:30:54,260
...the ring cannot stay here.

979
01:31:12,470 --> 01:31:15,869
This peril belongs to all Middle-earth.

980
01:31:15,870 --> 01:31:19,679
They must decide now how to end it.

981
01:31:19,680 --> 01:31:23,879
The time of the elves is over.
My people are leaving these shores.

982
01:31:23,880 --> 01:31:27,779
Who will you look to when we've gone?
The dwarves?

983
01:31:27,780 --> 01:31:34,180
They hide in mountains seeking riches.
They care not for the troubles of others.

984
01:31:34,380 --> 01:31:37,689
It is in men that we must place our hope.

985
01:31:37,690 --> 01:31:40,289
Men?

986
01:31:40,290 --> 01:31:43,689
Men are weak. The race of men is failing.

987
01:31:43,690 --> 01:31:48,389
The blood of Numenor is all but spent,
its pride and dignity forgotten.

988
01:31:48,390 --> 01:31:52,189
It is because of men the ring survives.

989
01:31:52,190 --> 01:31:54,499
I was there, Gandalf.

990
01:31:54,500 --> 01:31:58,700
I was there 3000 years ago...

991
01:32:04,100 --> 01:32:06,699
... when Isildur took the ring.

992
01:32:06,700 --> 01:32:11,900
I was there the day the strength of men failed.

993
01:32:13,110 --> 01:32:17,110
Isildur, hurry! Follow me.

994
01:32:17,310 --> 01:32:21,209
I led Isildur into the heart of Mount Doom...

995
01:32:21,210 --> 01:32:24,809
...where the ring was forged,
the one place it could be destroyed.

996
01:32:24,810 --> 01:32:28,810
Cast it into the fire!

997
01:32:32,620 --> 01:32:37,720
- Destroy it!
- No.

998
01:32:37,720 --> 01:32:40,319
Isildur!

999
01:32:40,320 --> 01:32:46,420
It should have ended that day,
but evil was allowed to endure.

1000
01:32:49,220 --> 01:32:54,329
Isildur kept the ring.
The line of kings is broken.

1001
01:32:54,330 --> 01:32:58,329
There's no strength left in the world of men.

1002
01:32:58,330 --> 01:33:03,329
- They're scattered, divided, leaderless.
- There is one who could unite them.

1003
01:33:03,330 --> 01:33:08,030
One who could reclaim the throne of Gondor.

1004
01:33:08,440 --> 01:33:12,339
He turned from that path a long time ago.

1005
01:33:12,340 --> 01:33:15,940
He has chosen exile.

1006
01:33:45,560 --> 01:33:47,759
You are no elf.

1007
01:33:47,760 --> 01:33:50,459
Men of the South are welcome here.

1008
01:33:50,460 --> 01:33:55,360
- Who are you?
- I am a friend to Gandalf the Grey.

1009
01:33:55,460 --> 01:33:58,559
Then we are here on common purpose...

1010
01:33:58,560 --> 01:34:01,460
...friend.

1011
01:34:15,370 --> 01:34:19,670
The shards of Narsil.

1012
01:34:21,780 --> 01:34:27,480
The blade that cut the ring from Sauron's hand.

1013
01:34:29,080 --> 01:34:32,780
It's still sharp.

1014
01:34:40,290 --> 01:34:44,690
But no more than a broken heirloom.

1015
01:35:10,200 --> 01:35:14,109
Why do you fear the past?

1016
01:35:14,110 --> 01:35:19,709
You are Isildur's heir, not Isildur himseIf.

1017
01:35:19,710 --> 01:35:23,609
You are not bound to his fate.

1018
01:35:23,610 --> 01:35:28,910
The same blood flows in my veins.

1019
01:35:30,620 --> 01:35:34,620
The same weakness.

1020
01:35:35,890 --> 01:35:38,889
Your time will come.

1021
01:35:38,890 --> 01:35:44,590
You will face the same evil.
And you will defeat it.

1022
01:35:46,180 --> 01:35:49,579
<font color="#008000">A si i-Dhuath ú-orthor, Aragorn.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Till now the Shadow not masters, Aragorn)</font>

1023
01:35:49,580 --> 01:35:54,880
<font color="#008000">Ú or le a ú or nin.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Not over you, not over me.)</font>

1024
01:36:00,233 --> 01:36:12,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ O môr henion i dhû</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(From darkness I understand the night)</font></i>

1025
01:36:04,770 --> 01:36:09,970
<font color="#008000">Renich i lú i erui govannem?</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Do you remember when we first met?)</font>

1026
01:36:12,233 --> 01:36:19,500
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Ely siriar, êl sila</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Dreams flow, a star shines)</font></i>

1027
01:36:12,270 --> 01:36:16,340
<font color="#008000">Nauthannen i ned ôl reniannen.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(I thought I had strayed into a dream.)</font>

1028
01:36:16,670 --> 01:36:19,500
<font color="#008000">Gwenwin in enninath.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Long years have passed.)</font>

1029
01:36:19,750 --> 01:36:48,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Ai! Aníron Undómiel</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Ah! I desire Evenstar)</font></i>

1030
01:36:19,760 --> 01:36:25,060
<font color="#008000">Ú-’arnech in naeth i si celich.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(You did not wear the troubles you carry now.)</font>

1031
01:36:25,760 --> 01:36:29,360
<font color="#008000">Renech i beth i pennen?</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Do you remember what I told you?)</font>

1032
01:36:33,760 --> 01:36:37,860
You said you'd bind yourself to me...

1033
01:36:38,560 --> 01:36:44,549
...forsaking the immortal life of your people.

1034
01:36:44,550 --> 01:36:46,649
And to that I hold.

1035
01:36:46,650 --> 01:36:50,649
I would rather share one lifetime with you...

1036
01:36:50,233 --> 01:37:01,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Tiro! El eria e môr</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Look! A star rises out of darkness)</font></i>

1037
01:36:50,650 --> 01:36:55,750
...than face all the ages of this world alone.

1038
01:37:02,233 --> 01:37:17,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ I ‘lîr en êl luitha ‘úren</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The song of the star enchants my heart)</font></i>

1039
01:37:03,140 --> 01:37:07,940
I choose a mortal life.

1040
01:37:07,940 --> 01:37:13,540
- You cannot give me this.
- It is mine to give to whom I will...

1041
01:37:15,440 --> 01:37:19,340
...like my heart.

1042
01:37:17,233 --> 01:37:32,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Ai! Aníron...</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Ah! I desire...)</font></i>

1043
01:37:33,730 --> 01:37:37,729
Strangers from distant lands, friends of old...

1044
01:37:37,730 --> 01:37:42,229
...you've been summoned here
to answer the threat of Mordor.

1045
01:37:42,230 --> 01:37:47,319
Middle-earth stands upon the brink of destruction.
None can escape it.

1046
01:37:47,320 --> 01:37:51,119
You will unite, or you will fall.

1047
01:37:51,120 --> 01:37:56,720
Each race is bound to this fate, this one doom.

1048
01:37:57,220 --> 01:38:02,020
Bring forth the ring, Frodo.

1049
01:38:14,810 --> 01:38:17,910
So it is true.

1050
01:38:26,200 --> 01:38:29,200
The ring of power...

1051
01:38:29,800 --> 01:38:32,800
The doom of men...

1052
01:38:33,900 --> 01:38:37,400
In a dream...

1053
01:38:37,700 --> 01:38:41,089
...I saw the eastern sky grow dark...

1054
01:38:41,090 --> 01:38:43,589
...but in the West a pale light lingered.

1055
01:38:43,590 --> 01:38:45,689
A voice was crying:

1056
01:38:45,690 --> 01:38:49,689
"Your doom is near at hand.

1057
01:38:49,690 --> 01:38:53,790
Isildur's bane is found."

1058
01:38:54,800 --> 01:38:56,200
<font color="#FF0000">Sherkuk-ishi</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(In your blood)</font>

1059
01:38:56,640 --> 01:38:58,440
Isildur's bane.

1060
01:38:58,680 --> 01:38:58,979
Boromir!

1061
01:38:58,980 --> 01:39:02,679
<font color="#FF0000">[Gandalf] Ash nazg durbatulûk</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(One ring to rule them all)</font>

1062
01:38:59,680 --> 01:39:05,600
<font color="#FF0000">[Sauron] Shre nazg golugranu kilmi-nudu</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Three Rings for the Elven-kings under the sky)</font>

1063
01:39:02,680 --> 01:39:06,400
<font color="#FF0000">[Gandalf] Ash nazg gimbatul</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(One ring to find them)</font>

1064
01:39:05,881 --> 01:39:10,400
<font color="#FF0000">[Sauron] Ombi kuzd-durbagu... sherkuk</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Seven for the Dwarf-lords... blood)</font>

1065
01:39:06,650 --> 01:39:11,800
<font color="#FF0000">[Gandalf] Ash nazg thrakatuluk</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(One ring to bring them all)</font>

1066
01:39:10,681 --> 01:39:16,500
<font color="#FF0000">[Sauron] Ash burz durbagu burzum-ishi</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(One for the Dark Lord on his dark throne)</font>

1067
01:39:12,580 --> 01:39:18,580
<font color="#FF0000">[Gandalf] Agh burzum-ishi krimpatul.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(and in the darkness bind them.)</font>

1068
01:39:23,170 --> 01:39:27,269
Never before has any voice uttered the
words of that tongue here in Imladris.

1069
01:39:27,270 --> 01:39:31,069
I do not ask your pardon, Master Elrond...

1070
01:39:31,070 --> 01:39:33,469
...for the black speech of Mordor...

1071
01:39:33,470 --> 01:39:35,069
...may yet be heard...

1072
01:39:35,070 --> 01:39:38,169
...in every corner of the West!

1073
01:39:38,170 --> 01:39:41,269
The ring is altogether evil.

1074
01:39:41,270 --> 01:39:43,459
It is a gift.

1075
01:39:43,460 --> 01:39:46,059
A gift to the foes of Mordor.

1076
01:39:46,060 --> 01:39:48,359
Why not use this ring?

1077
01:39:48,360 --> 01:39:51,359
Long has my father, the Steward of Gondor...

1078
01:39:51,360 --> 01:39:55,959
...kept the forces of Mordor at bay.
By the blood of our people...

1079
01:39:55,960 --> 01:39:59,560
...are your lands kept safe.

1080
01:39:59,860 --> 01:40:04,449
Give Gondor the weapon of the enemy.
Let us use it against him.

1081
01:40:04,450 --> 01:40:08,849
You cannot wield it. None of us can.

1082
01:40:08,850 --> 01:40:13,149
The one ring answers to Sauron alone.
It has no other master.

1083
01:40:13,150 --> 01:40:16,849
And what would a ranger know of this matter?

1084
01:40:16,850 --> 01:40:19,839
This is no mere ranger.

1085
01:40:19,840 --> 01:40:24,039
He is Aragorn, son of Arathorn.

1086
01:40:24,040 --> 01:40:28,340
You owe him your allegiance.

1087
01:40:31,040 --> 01:40:34,440
Aragorn.

1088
01:40:34,740 --> 01:40:39,040
This is Isildur's heir?

1089
01:40:39,940 --> 01:40:44,140
And heir to the throne of Gondor.

1090
01:40:44,230 --> 01:40:47,930
<font color="#008000">Havo dad, Legolas.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Sit down, Legolas.)</font>

1091
01:40:49,530 --> 01:40:53,830
Gondor has no king.

1092
01:40:54,330 --> 01:40:57,430
Gondor needs no king.

1093
01:41:02,620 --> 01:41:07,319
Aragorn is right. We cannot use it.

1094
01:41:07,320 --> 01:41:10,919
You have only one choice.

1095
01:41:10,920 --> 01:41:14,720
The ring must be destroyed.

1096
01:41:18,520 --> 01:41:22,520
Then what are we waiting for?

1097
01:41:26,550 --> 01:41:32,550
<font color="#FF0000">...Daghburz-ishi makha gulshu... sherkuk</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">...In the Land of Mordor where the Shadows... blood</font>

1098
01:41:33,470 --> 01:41:36,769
The ring cannot be destroyed, Gimli, son of Gloin...

1099
01:41:36,770 --> 01:41:41,569
...by any craft that we here possess.

1100
01:41:41,570 --> 01:41:45,659
The ring was made in the fires of Mount Doom.

1101
01:41:45,859 --> 01:41:50,640
<i><font color="#FF0000">[Daghburz]-ishi makha gulshu darulu</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">In the Land of Mordor where the Shadows lie</font></i>

1102
01:41:45,860 --> 01:41:50,659
Only there can it be unmade.

1103
01:41:50,860 --> 01:41:53,559
It must be taken deep into Mordor...

1104
01:41:53,560 --> 01:41:58,059
...and cast back into the fiery
chasm from whence it came.

1105
01:41:58,060 --> 01:42:01,220
<i><font color="#FF0000">[Daghburz]-ishi makha gulshu darulu</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">In the Land of Mordor where the Shadows lie</font></i>

1106
01:42:01,250 --> 01:42:03,049
One of you...

1107
01:42:03,050 --> 01:42:06,650
...must do this.

1108
01:42:08,150 --> 01:42:12,749
One does not simply walk into Mordor.

1109
01:42:12,750 --> 01:42:17,139
Its black gates are guarded by more than just orcs.

1110
01:42:17,140 --> 01:42:21,539
There is evil there that does not sleep.

1111
01:42:21,540 --> 01:42:26,529
The great eye is ever-watchful.

1112
01:42:26,530 --> 01:42:28,829
It is a barren wasteland...

1113
01:42:28,830 --> 01:42:32,529
...riddled with fire, and ash and dust.

1114
01:42:32,530 --> 01:42:36,629
The very air you breathe is a poisonous fume.

1115
01:42:36,630 --> 01:42:41,129
Not with 10,000 men could you do this.
It is folly.

1116
01:42:41,130 --> 01:42:45,819
Have you heard nothing Lord Elrond has said?
The ring must be destroyed.

1117
01:42:45,820 --> 01:42:48,519
And I suppose you think you are the one to do it!

1118
01:42:48,520 --> 01:42:53,419
And if we fail, what then? What happens
when Sauron takes back what is his?

1119
01:42:53,420 --> 01:43:00,020
I will be dead before I see the
ring in the hands of an elf!

1120
01:43:00,710 --> 01:43:04,409
Never trust an elf!

1121
01:43:04,410 --> 01:43:10,509
Do you not understand? While you bicker
amongst yourselves, Sauron's power grows!

1122
01:43:10,510 --> 01:43:14,399
None can escape it!
You'll all be destroyed!

1123
01:43:14,400 --> 01:43:16,799
<i><font color="#FF0000">Ash nazg durbatuluk...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(One ring to rule them all...)</font></i>

1124
01:43:16,800 --> 01:43:19,299
<i><font color="#FF0000">Ash nazg gimbatul...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(One ring to find them...)</font></i>

1125
01:43:19,300 --> 01:43:21,399
<i><font color="#FF0000">Ash nazg durbatuluk...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(One ring to rule them all...)</font></i>

1126
01:43:21,400 --> 01:43:23,499
<i><font color="#FF0000">Ash nazg gimbatul...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(One ring to find them...)</font></i>

1127
01:43:23,500 --> 01:43:25,489
<i><font color="#FF0000">Ash nazg durbatuluk...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(One ring to rule them all...)</font></i>

1128
01:43:25,490 --> 01:43:27,589
<i><font color="#FF0000">Ash nazg gimbatul...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(One ring to find them...)</font></i>

1129
01:43:27,590 --> 01:43:31,090
<i><font color="#FF0000">Ash nazg durbatuluk...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(One ring to rule them all...)</font></i>

1130
01:43:32,090 --> 01:43:35,590
I will take it.

1131
01:43:36,390 --> 01:43:40,390
I will take it.

1132
01:43:44,680 --> 01:43:49,180
I will take the ring to Mordor.

1133
01:43:55,970 --> 01:43:58,570
Though...

1134
01:44:00,270 --> 01:44:03,570
...I do not know the way.

1135
01:44:04,070 --> 01:44:08,559
I will help you bear this burden, Frodo Baggins...

1136
01:44:08,560 --> 01:44:13,059
...as long as it is yours to bear.

1137
01:44:13,060 --> 01:44:16,859
If by my life or death I can protect you...

1138
01:44:16,860 --> 01:44:19,660
...I will.

1139
01:44:21,460 --> 01:44:25,160
You have my sword.

1140
01:44:25,550 --> 01:44:28,249
And you have my bow.

1141
01:44:28,250 --> 01:44:32,050
And my ax.

1142
01:44:37,740 --> 01:44:42,040
You carry the fates of us all, little one.

1143
01:44:42,740 --> 01:44:46,939
If this is indeed the will of the Council...

1144
01:44:46,940 --> 01:44:50,840
...then Gondor will see it done.

1145
01:44:51,940 --> 01:44:56,929
- Mr. Frodo's not going anywhere without me.
- No indeed it is hardly possible to separate you...

1146
01:44:56,930 --> 01:45:02,329
...even when he is summoned to a
secret council and you are not.

1147
01:45:02,330 --> 01:45:05,630
Oy. We're coming too!

1148
01:45:06,320 --> 01:45:09,219
You'll have to send us home
tied up in a sack to stop us.

1149
01:45:09,220 --> 01:45:12,919
Anyway, you need people
of intelligence on this sort of...

1150
01:45:12,920 --> 01:45:14,519
...mission.

1151
01:45:14,520 --> 01:45:16,419
Quest.

1152
01:45:16,420 --> 01:45:18,920
Thing.

1153
01:45:19,220 --> 01:45:23,420
Well, that rules you out, Pip.

1154
01:45:23,610 --> 01:45:26,910
Nine companions.

1155
01:45:27,210 --> 01:45:29,409
So be it.

1156
01:45:29,410 --> 01:45:33,109
You shall be: The Fellowship of the Ring.

1157
01:45:33,110 --> 01:45:35,309
Great!

1158
01:45:35,310 --> 01:45:38,910
Where are we going?

1159
01:45:49,970 --> 01:46:01,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Estel le iôn adar lín</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(You are your father’s son)</font></i>

1160
01:46:02,970 --> 01:46:12,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Û iôn naneth lín</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Not your mother’s child)</font></i>

1161
01:46:11,870 --> 01:46:16,159
<font color="#008000">Anirne hene beriad i chen lîn.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(She wanted to protect her child.)</font>

1162
01:46:13,970 --> 01:46:27,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ A chéneg a ionneg</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Little boy, little one)</font></i>

1163
01:46:16,160 --> 01:46:21,060
<font color="#008000">Ned Imladris nauthant e le beriathar aen.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(She thought in Rivendell you would be safe.)</font>

1164
01:46:22,560 --> 01:46:26,569
In her heart, your mother knew
you'd be hunted all your life.

1165
01:46:26,570 --> 01:46:28,569
That you'd never escape your fate.

1166
01:46:28,750 --> 01:46:35,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Danna si (fuin)</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Night is falling)</font></i>

1167
01:46:28,770 --> 01:46:32,850
The skill of the elves can reforge
the sword of kings...

1168
01:46:32,870 --> 01:46:36,100
...but only you have the power to wield it.

1169
01:46:36,370 --> 01:46:45,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Tolo na rengy</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Come into my arms)</font></i>

1170
01:46:37,770 --> 01:46:40,469
I do not want that power.

1171
01:46:40,470 --> 01:46:44,369
I have never wanted it.

1172
01:46:44,370 --> 01:46:48,370
You are the last of that bloodline.
There is no other.

1173
01:46:46,970 --> 01:46:54,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ne theilien</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Slaying demons in the shadows)</font></i>

1174
01:46:51,570 --> 01:46:54,169
My old sword! Sting.

1175
01:46:54,170 --> 01:46:56,770
Here, take it. Take it.

1176
01:47:00,670 --> 01:47:05,269
- It's so light.
- Yes, yeah. Made by the elves, you know.

1177
01:47:05,270 --> 01:47:09,769
The blade glows blue when orcs are close.

1178
01:47:09,770 --> 01:47:14,469
And it's times like that, my lad,
when you have to be extra careful.

1179
01:47:14,470 --> 01:47:17,369
Here's a pretty thing.

1180
01:47:17,370 --> 01:47:19,469
Mithril.

1181
01:47:19,470 --> 01:47:24,069
As light as a feather, and as hard as dragon scales.

1182
01:47:24,070 --> 01:47:28,670
Let me see you put it on. Come on.

1183
01:47:35,370 --> 01:47:38,669
My old ring.

1184
01:47:38,670 --> 01:47:42,869
I should very much like...

1185
01:47:42,870 --> 01:47:48,170
...to hold it again, one last time.

1186
01:48:04,180 --> 01:48:08,179
I'm sorry I brought this upon you, my boy.

1187
01:48:08,180 --> 01:48:13,580
I'm sorry that you must carry this burden.

1188
01:48:16,880 --> 01:48:21,280
I'm sorry for everything.

1189
01:48:34,780 --> 01:48:40,379
The ring-bearer is setting out
on the quest of Mount Doom.

1190
01:48:40,380 --> 01:48:43,279
On you who travel with him, no oath...

1191
01:48:43,280 --> 01:48:47,780
...nor bond is laid to go further than you will.

1192
01:48:49,780 --> 01:48:52,679
Farewell. Hold to your purpose.

1193
01:48:52,680 --> 01:48:57,279
May the blessings of elves and men...

1194
01:48:57,280 --> 01:49:01,280
...and all free folk go with you.

1195
01:49:02,880 --> 01:49:08,280
The fellowship awaits the ring-bearer.

1196
01:49:25,480 --> 01:49:28,479
Mordor, Gandalf, is it left or right?

1197
01:49:28,600 --> 01:49:36,200
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Uilos le linnathon</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(I will sing to you)</font></i>

1198
01:49:28,620 --> 01:49:31,780
Left.

1199
01:49:36,600 --> 01:49:53,200
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Nef aear sî nef aearon</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Beyond the Sea, beyond the wide and sundering Sea)</font></i>

1200
01:50:49,990 --> 01:50:54,589
We must hold to this course, west
of the Misty Mountains, for 40 days.

1201
01:50:54,590 --> 01:50:58,589
If our luck holds, the Gap of Rohan
will still be open to us.

1202
01:50:58,590 --> 01:51:02,289
From there, our road turns east to Mordor.

1203
01:51:02,290 --> 01:51:07,490
Two, one, five. Good! Very good.

1204
01:51:07,990 --> 01:51:09,189
Move your feet.

1205
01:51:09,190 --> 01:51:10,789
- You look good, Pippin.
- Thanks.

1206
01:51:10,790 --> 01:51:13,489
Faster!

1207
01:51:13,490 --> 01:51:17,489
If anyone was to ask for my opinion,
which I note they're not...

1208
01:51:17,490 --> 01:51:20,789
...I'd say we were taking the long way 'round.

1209
01:51:20,790 --> 01:51:24,389
Gandalf.
We could pass through the mines of Moria.

1210
01:51:24,390 --> 01:51:28,489
My cousin Balin would give us a royal welcome.

1211
01:51:28,490 --> 01:51:35,190
No Gimli, I would not take the road through
Moria unless I had no other choice.

1212
01:51:43,200 --> 01:51:44,989
Sorry!

1213
01:51:44,990 --> 01:51:47,990
Get him!

1214
01:51:48,000 --> 01:51:50,999
- For the Shire!
- Hold him. Hold him down, Merry!

1215
01:51:51,000 --> 01:51:54,700
Gentlemen, that's enough.

1216
01:51:57,100 --> 01:51:59,099
You've got my arm!
You've got my arm!

1217
01:51:59,100 --> 01:52:02,099
- What is that?
- Nothing. It's just a wisp of cloud.

1218
01:52:02,100 --> 01:52:04,999
It's moving fast.

1219
01:52:05,000 --> 01:52:07,899
Against the wind.

1220
01:52:07,900 --> 01:52:10,299
- Crebain from Dunland!
- Hide!

1221
01:52:10,300 --> 01:52:14,400
- Hurry!
- Take cover!

1222
01:52:46,500 --> 01:52:48,899
Spies of Saruman.

1223
01:52:48,900 --> 01:52:53,299
The passage south is being watched.

1224
01:52:53,300 --> 01:52:58,100
We must take the pass of Caradhras.

1225
01:53:09,200 --> 01:53:12,300
Frodo!

1226
01:53:29,733 --> 01:53:42,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ I tuo I macil staldaron</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The strength, the weapon, the needs of the valiant)</font></i>

1227
01:53:29,900 --> 01:53:32,399
Boromir.

1228
01:53:32,400 --> 01:53:36,809
It is a strange fate that we should
suffer so much fear and doubt...

1229
01:53:36,810 --> 01:53:41,310
...over so small a thing.

1230
01:53:42,233 --> 01:53:47,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Marinyë túren</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The mean of victory)</font></i>

1231
01:53:43,210 --> 01:53:45,409
Such a little thing.

1232
01:53:45,410 --> 01:53:47,509
Boromir!

1233
01:53:47,510 --> 01:53:51,510
Give the ring to Frodo.

1234
01:54:00,010 --> 01:54:02,709
As you wish.

1235
01:54:02,710 --> 01:54:06,210
I care not.

1236
01:54:40,110 --> 01:54:45,009
So, Gandalf, you try to lead them over Caradhras.

1237
01:54:45,010 --> 01:54:51,010
And if that fails, where then will you go?

1238
01:54:51,010 --> 01:54:54,109
If the mountain defeats you...

1239
01:54:54,110 --> 01:54:59,910
... will you risk a more dangerous road?

1240
01:55:03,710 --> 01:55:11,009
<i><font color="#0080C0">Cuiva nwalca Carnirassë!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Wake up cruel Redhorn!)</font></i>

1241
01:55:11,010 --> 01:55:13,809
There is a fell voice on the air.

1242
01:55:13,810 --> 01:55:20,009
<i><font color="#0080C0">Nai yarvaxëa rasselya!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(May your horn be bloodstained!)</font></i>

1243
01:55:15,010 --> 01:55:17,910
It's Saruman!

1244
01:55:25,420 --> 01:55:30,219
He's trying to bring down the mountain!
Gandalf, we must turn back!

1245
01:55:30,220 --> 01:55:33,520
No!

1246
01:55:34,120 --> 01:55:40,419
<font color="#0080C0">Losto Caradhras, sedho, hodo, nuitho i ’ruith!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Sleep Caradhras, be still, lie still, hold your wrath!)</font>

1247
01:55:40,420 --> 01:55:45,619
<i><font color="#0080C0">Cuiva nwalca Carnirassë!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Wake up cruel Redhorn!)</font></i>

1248
01:55:45,620 --> 01:55:50,119
<font color="#0080C0">Nai yarvaxëa rasselya...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(May your bloodstained horn...)</font>

1249
01:55:50,120 --> 01:55:55,120
<font color="#0080C0">...taltuva ñotto-carinnar!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(...fall upon the enemy-heads!)</font>

1250
01:56:38,520 --> 01:56:40,819
We must get off the mountain!

1251
01:56:40,820 --> 01:56:45,419
Make for the Gap of Rohan,
and take the west road to my city!

1252
01:56:45,420 --> 01:56:48,919
The Gap of Rohan takes us too close to Isengard!

1253
01:56:48,920 --> 01:56:52,919
We cannot pass over a mountain.
Let us go under it.

1254
01:56:52,920 --> 01:56:57,120
Let us go through the mines of Moria.

1255
01:56:57,520 --> 01:57:02,019
Moria. You fear to go into those mines.

1256
01:57:02,020 --> 01:57:07,919
The dwarves delved too greedily and too deep.

1257
01:57:07,920 --> 01:57:14,019
You know what they awoke
in the darkness of Khazad-dûm:

1258
01:57:14,020 --> 01:57:18,820
Shadow and flame.

1259
01:57:20,920 --> 01:57:25,020
Let the ring-bearer decide.

1260
01:57:28,330 --> 01:57:30,629
We cannot stay here!

1261
01:57:30,630 --> 01:57:33,629
This will be the death of the hobbits.

1262
01:57:33,630 --> 01:57:36,730
Frodo?

1263
01:57:38,330 --> 01:57:42,029
We will go through the mines.

1264
01:57:42,030 --> 01:57:45,330
So be it.

1265
01:57:50,530 --> 01:57:55,730
Frodo, come and help an old man.

1266
01:57:57,930 --> 01:58:00,329
How is your shoulder?

1267
01:58:00,330 --> 01:58:04,930
- Better than it was.
- And the ring?

1268
01:58:05,130 --> 01:58:08,129
You feel its power growing, don't you?

1269
01:58:08,130 --> 01:58:11,529
I've felt it too.
You must be careful now.

1270
01:58:11,530 --> 01:58:15,529
Evil will be drawn to you from
outside the fellowship.

1271
01:58:15,530 --> 01:58:19,530
And, I fear, from within.

1272
01:58:20,830 --> 01:58:25,129
- Who then do I trust?
- You must trust yourself.

1273
01:58:25,130 --> 01:58:28,229
Trust your own strengths.

1274
01:58:28,230 --> 01:58:30,929
- What do you mean?
- There are many powers in this world...

1275
01:58:30,930 --> 01:58:33,229
...for good or for evil.

1276
01:58:33,230 --> 01:58:36,029
Some are greater than I am.

1277
01:58:36,030 --> 01:58:40,930
And against some I have not yet been tested.

1278
01:58:41,030 --> 01:58:43,129
The walls...

1279
01:58:43,130 --> 01:58:46,630
...of Moria.

1280
01:58:50,930 --> 01:58:54,129
Dwarf doors are invisible when closed.

1281
01:58:54,130 --> 01:58:58,929
Yes, Gimli, their own masters cannot find
them if their secrets are forgotten.

1282
01:58:58,930 --> 01:59:02,830
Why doesn't that surprise me?

1283
01:59:09,330 --> 01:59:12,929
Well, let's see.

1284
01:59:12,930 --> 01:59:15,039
<font color="#008000">Ithildin.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(“moon-star”)</font>

1285
01:59:15,040 --> 01:59:19,740
It mirrors only starlight and moonlight.

1286
01:59:21,233 --> 01:59:40,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Man ammen toltha</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Who brings <b>this</b>?)</font></i>

1287
01:59:32,440 --> 01:59:37,139
It reads; "The Doors of Durin, Lord of Moria.

1288
01:59:37,140 --> 01:59:41,900
- Speak, friend, and enter."
- What do you suppose that means?

1289
01:59:42,000 --> 01:59:54,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Si danna atha</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(All will fall away)</font></i>

1290
01:59:42,040 --> 01:59:47,239
Oh It's quite simple. If you are a friend,
you speak the password and the doors will open.

1291
01:59:47,240 --> 01:59:53,840
<font color="#008000">Annon Edhellen, edro hi ammen!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Gate of the elves, open now for me!)</font>

1292
01:59:59,500 --> 02:00:01,500
<font color="#008000">Fennas Nogothrim...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Doorway of the dwarf-folk...)</font>

1293
02:00:03,040 --> 02:00:08,440
<font color="#008000">lasto beth lammen.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(listen to the word of my tongue.)</font>

1294
02:00:10,440 --> 02:00:12,940
Nothing's happening.

1295
02:00:18,640 --> 02:00:23,139
I once knew every spell in
all the tongues of elves...

1296
02:00:23,140 --> 02:00:26,139
...men and orcs.

1297
02:00:26,140 --> 02:00:27,539
What are you going to do, then?

1298
02:00:27,540 --> 02:00:30,039
Knock your head against these doors,
Peregrin Took!

1299
02:00:30,040 --> 02:00:32,239
And if that does not shatter them...

1300
02:00:32,240 --> 02:00:35,139
...and I am allowed a little
peace from foolish questions...

1301
02:00:35,140 --> 02:00:39,940
...I will try to find the opening words.

1302
02:00:42,040 --> 02:00:45,540
<font color="#0080C0">Ando Eldarinwa...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Gate of elves...)</font>

1303
02:00:45,740 --> 02:00:48,739
<font color="#0080C0">a lasta quettanya...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(listen to my word...)</font>

1304
02:00:48,740 --> 02:00:51,439
<font color="#0080C0">Fenda Casarinwa!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(threshold of dwarves!)</font>

1305
02:00:51,440 --> 02:00:54,239
Mines are no place for a pony.

1306
02:00:54,240 --> 02:00:58,239
- Even one so brave as Bill.
- Bye-bye, Bill.

1307
02:00:58,240 --> 02:00:59,539
<font color="#008000">Fennas Nogothrim...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Doorway of the dwarf-folk...)</font>

1308
02:00:59,540 --> 02:01:02,849
Go on, Bill. Go on.

1309
02:01:02,850 --> 02:01:07,850
Don't worry, Sam, he knows the way home.

1310
02:01:13,250 --> 02:01:15,949
Do not disturb the water.

1311
02:01:15,950 --> 02:01:19,350
Oh, it's useless.

1312
02:01:30,550 --> 02:01:34,150
It's a riddle.

1313
02:01:35,450 --> 02:01:39,049
"Speak 'friend' and enter."

1314
02:01:39,050 --> 02:01:43,249
What's the elvish word for "friend"?

1315
02:01:43,250 --> 02:01:46,050
<font color="#008000">Mellon.</font>

1316
02:02:02,650 --> 02:02:07,949
Soon, master elf, you will enjoy
the fabled hospitality of the dwarves.

1317
02:02:07,950 --> 02:02:14,950
Roaring fires, malt beer, ripe meat off the bone!

1318
02:02:15,250 --> 02:02:18,749
This, my friend, is the home of my cousin Balin.

1319
02:02:18,750 --> 02:02:21,249
And they call it a mine.

1320
02:02:21,250 --> 02:02:24,349
A mine!

1321
02:02:24,350 --> 02:02:28,950
This is no mine. It's a tomb.

1322
02:02:33,750 --> 02:02:36,559
No....

1323
02:02:36,560 --> 02:02:39,660
No!

1324
02:02:40,950 --> 02:02:43,850
Goblins.

1325
02:02:46,350 --> 02:02:51,649
We make for the Gap of Rohan.
We should never have come here.

1326
02:02:51,650 --> 02:02:55,650
Now, get out of here. Get out!

1327
02:02:57,050 --> 02:02:59,759
- Frodo!
- Help!

1328
02:02:59,760 --> 02:03:01,459
Strider!

1329
02:03:01,460 --> 02:03:04,359
- Help!
- Get off him!

1330
02:03:04,360 --> 02:03:06,860
Aragorn!

1331
02:03:15,860 --> 02:03:18,360
Frodo!

1332
02:03:43,160 --> 02:03:44,459
Into the mines!

1333
02:03:44,460 --> 02:03:49,060
- Legolas!
- Into the cave!

1334
02:03:51,960 --> 02:03:55,160
Run!

1335
02:04:10,660 --> 02:04:14,459
We now have but one choice.

1336
02:04:14,460 --> 02:04:19,559
We must face the long dark of Moria.

1337
02:04:19,560 --> 02:04:21,759
Be on your guard.

1338
02:04:21,760 --> 02:04:25,459
There are older and fouler things than orcs...

1339
02:04:25,460 --> 02:04:30,260
...in the deep places of the world.

1340
02:04:36,860 --> 02:04:41,069
Quietly now.
It's a four-day journey to the other side.

1341
02:04:41,333 --> 02:04:50,200
<i><font color="#FF8000">♫ Durin ku bin-amrad</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Durin who is Deathless)</font></i>

1342
02:04:41,335 --> 02:04:46,170
Let us hope that our presence may go unnoticed.

1343
02:04:50,533 --> 02:04:58,200
<i><font color="#FF8000">♫ Ugmal sullu addad</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Eldest of all Fathers)</font></i>

1344
02:05:03,533 --> 02:05:16,200
<i><font color="#FF8000">♫ Ku bakana</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Beneath the mountain)</font></i>

1345
02:05:18,533 --> 02:05:28,200
<i><font color="#FF8000">♫ Ana aznân...</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Who awoke...)</font></i>

1346
