02:35:01,330 --> 02:35:05,029
I can no longer see him from afar.

1556
02:35:05,030 --> 02:35:10,429
Gandalf the Grey did not pass
the borders of this land.

1557
02:35:10,430 --> 02:35:14,230
He has fallen into shadow.

1558
02:35:17,530 --> 02:35:23,330
He was taken by both shadow and flame.

1559
02:35:23,730 --> 02:35:28,129
A Balrog of Morgoth.

1560
02:35:28,130 --> 02:35:32,930
For we went needlessly into the net of Moria.

1561
02:35:33,630 --> 02:35:37,529
Needless were none of the deeds of Gandalf in life.

1562
02:35:37,530 --> 02:35:42,230
We do not yet know his full purpose.

1563
02:35:45,530 --> 02:35:50,029
Do not let the great emptiness
of Khazad-dûm fill your heart...

1564
02:35:50,030 --> 02:35:53,329
...Gimli, son of Gloin.

1565
02:35:53,330 --> 02:35:58,230
For the world has grown full of peril...

1566
02:35:58,330 --> 02:36:01,229
...and in all lands...

1567
02:36:01,230 --> 02:36:06,130
...love is now mingled with grief.

1568
02:36:17,330 --> 02:36:20,729
What now becomes of this fellowship?

1569
02:36:20,730 --> 02:36:25,030
Without Gandalf, hope is lost.

1570
02:36:26,630 --> 02:36:30,029
The quest stands upon the edge of a knife.

1571
02:36:30,030 --> 02:36:33,929
Stray but a little and it will fail...

1572
02:36:33,930 --> 02:36:38,130
...to the ruin of all.

1573
02:36:41,130 --> 02:36:48,130
Yet hope remains while the company is true.

1574
02:36:48,440 --> 02:36:53,539
Do not let your hearts be troubled.
Go now and rest...

1575
02:36:53,540 --> 02:36:58,640
...for you are weary with sorrow and much toil.

1576
02:36:59,540 --> 02:37:01,939
Tonight, you will sleep....

1577
02:37:01,940 --> 02:37:06,740
<i>Welcome, Frodo of the Shire...</i>

1578
02:37:06,840 --> 02:37:10,040
<i>...one who has seen the eye!</i>

1579
02:37:11,200 --> 02:37:14,040
<i><font color="#008000">♫ In gwidh ristennin,</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The bonds cut)</font></i>

1580
02:37:14,840 --> 02:37:22,040
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Ilfirin nairelma</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Undying is our regret)</font></i>

1581
02:37:22,840 --> 02:37:30,040
<i><font color="#008000">♫ I fae narchannen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The spirit broken)</font></i>

1582
02:37:23,240 --> 02:37:27,240
A lament for Gandalf.

1583
02:37:30,840 --> 02:37:35,040
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Nauva i nauva</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(what should be shall be)</font></i>

1584
02:37:33,140 --> 02:37:35,000
What do they say about him?

1585
02:37:35,020 --> 02:37:38,940
I have not the heart to tell you.

1586
02:37:35,840 --> 02:37:41,040
<i><font color="#008000">♫ I Lach Anor ed</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The Flame of Anor)</font></i>

1587
02:37:41,540 --> 02:37:48,040
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Ilfirin nairelma</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Undying is our regret)</font></i>

1588
02:37:41,640 --> 02:37:44,140
For me, the grief is still too near.

1589
02:37:45,640 --> 02:37:48,839
I bet they don't mention his fireworks.

1590
02:37:48,840 --> 02:37:55,040
<i><font color="#008000">♫ ardhon gwannen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(has left this World)</font></i>

1591
02:37:48,850 --> 02:37:53,140
There should be a verse about them.

1592
02:37:55,640 --> 02:37:59,040
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Ar ullume nucuvalme</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(and yet we will cast all away)</font></i>

1593
02:37:55,840 --> 02:37:58,239
The finest rockets ever seen

1594
02:37:58,240 --> 02:37:59,639
They burst in stars of blue and green

1595
02:37:59,840 --> 02:38:07,800
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Mithrandir A Randir Vithren!</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Mithrandir, O Pilgrim Grey!)</font></i>

1596
02:38:02,140 --> 02:38:07,900
Or after thunder, silver showers

1597
02:38:08,000 --> 02:38:11,040
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Nauva i nauva</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(What should be shall be)</font></i>

1598
02:38:08,200 --> 02:38:11,039
Came falling like a rain of flowers

1599
02:38:11,640 --> 02:38:19,040
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ú-reniathach</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(No more you will)</font></i>

1600
02:38:11,840 --> 02:38:16,240
Oh, that doesn't do them justice by a long road.

1601
02:38:19,840 --> 02:38:24,040
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Nauva i nauva</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(What should be shall be)</font></i>

1602
02:38:24,840 --> 02:38:32,040
<i><font color="#008000">♫ I amar galen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Wander the green fields of this earth)</font></i>

1603
02:38:25,650 --> 02:38:28,539
Take some rest.

1604
02:38:28,540 --> 02:38:31,439
These borders are well-protected.

1605
02:38:31,440 --> 02:38:35,340
I will find no rest here.

1606
02:38:36,840 --> 02:38:43,400
<i><font color="#008000">♫ I reniad lín ne môr</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Your journey has ended in darkness)</font></i>

1607
02:38:36,940 --> 02:38:40,139
I heard her voice inside my head.

1608
02:38:40,140 --> 02:38:43,400
She spoke of my father and the fall of Gondor.

1609
02:38:43,840 --> 02:38:50,040
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ melme nóren</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(our love for this land)</font></i>

1610
02:38:43,950 --> 02:38:50,650
She said to me; "Even now there is hope left."

1611
02:38:50,840 --> 02:38:53,040
<i><font color="#008000">♫ nuithannen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(in darknes.)</font></i>

1612
02:38:50,940 --> 02:38:54,740
But I cannot see it.

1613
02:38:54,840 --> 02:38:59,040
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ sina nairelma</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(is our regret)</font></i>

1614
02:38:54,940 --> 02:38:58,840
It is long since we had any hope.

1615
02:39:07,650 --> 02:39:10,549
My father is a noble man.

1616
02:39:10,550 --> 02:39:14,250
But his rule is failing...

1617
02:39:15,950 --> 02:39:19,850
...and our people lose faith.

1618
02:39:19,950 --> 02:39:23,649
He looks to me to make things right,
and I would do it.

1619
02:39:23,650 --> 02:39:28,550
I would see the glory of Gondor restored.

1620
02:39:30,050 --> 02:39:33,649
Have you ever seen it, Aragorn?

1621
02:39:33,650 --> 02:39:35,949
The white tower of Ecthelion.

1622
02:39:35,950 --> 02:39:40,349
Glimmering like a spike of pearl and silver.

1623
02:39:40,350 --> 02:39:45,250
Its banners caught high in the morning breeze.

1624
02:39:46,850 --> 02:39:48,949
Have you ever been called home...

1625
02:39:48,950 --> 02:39:53,549
...by the clear ringing of silver trumpets?

1626
02:39:53,550 --> 02:39:57,049
I have seen the white city...

1627
02:39:57,050 --> 02:39:59,549
...long ago.

1628
02:39:59,550 --> 02:40:05,449
One day, our paths will lead us there.

1629
02:40:05,450 --> 02:40:08,949
And the tower guard shall take up the call:

1630
02:40:08,950 --> 02:40:13,550
"The Lords of Gondor have returned."

1631
02:40:37,233 --> 02:40:47,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Si danna atha nauva</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Now all will fall away)</font></i>

1632
02:40:48,233 --> 02:40:58,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Melmelma nóren sina</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Our love for this land)</font></i>

1633
02:40:59,233 --> 02:41:11,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Núra [lá] earo núri</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(is deeper than the depths of the sea)</font></i>

1634
02:41:12,233 --> 02:41:19,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Ilfirin nairelma</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Undying is our regret)</font></i>

1635
02:41:19,233 --> 02:41:28,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ I nairelma nauva</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Our regret will be)</font></i>

1636
02:41:19,460 --> 02:41:22,159
Will you look into the mirror?

1637
02:41:22,160 --> 02:41:25,060
What will I see?

1638
02:41:26,660 --> 02:41:29,659
Even the wisest cannot tell.

1639
02:41:29,833 --> 02:41:43,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Núra [lá] earo</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(deeper than the deeps of the sea)</font></i>

1640
02:41:29,860 --> 02:41:31,959
For the mirror...

1641
02:41:31,960 --> 02:41:35,860
...shows many things.

1642
02:41:37,460 --> 02:41:40,059
Things that were...

1643
02:41:40,060 --> 02:41:43,359
...things that are...

1644
02:41:43,360 --> 02:41:46,660
...and some things...

1645
02:41:48,960 --> 02:41:53,660
...that have not yet come to pass.

1646
02:43:14,770 --> 02:43:19,070
I know what it is you saw.

1647
02:43:20,070 --> 02:43:23,870
For it is also in my mind.

1648
02:43:24,370 --> 02:43:29,670
<i>It is what will come to pass if you should fail.</i>

1649
02:43:30,770 --> 02:43:36,269
<i>The fellowship is breaking.
It is already begun.</i>

1650
02:43:36,270 --> 02:43:39,769
<i>He will try to take the ring.</i>

1651
02:43:39,770 --> 02:43:42,769
<i>You know of whom I speak.</i>

1652
02:43:42,770 --> 02:43:48,670
<i>One by one, it will destroy them all.</i>

1653
02:43:48,970 --> 02:43:51,769
<i>If you ask it of me...</i>

1654
02:43:51,770 --> 02:43:55,969
<i>... I will give you the one ring.</i>

1655
02:43:55,970 --> 02:43:59,570
<i>You offer it to me freely.</i>

1656
02:44:02,570 --> 02:44:07,870
<i>I do not deny that my heart
has greatly desired this.</i>

1657
02:44:13,070 --> 02:44:16,669
In place of a dark lord, you would have a queen...

1658
02:44:16,670 --> 02:44:21,169
...not dark but beautiful and terrible as the dawn!

1659
02:44:21,170 --> 02:44:24,579
Treacherous as the sea!

1660
02:44:24,580 --> 02:44:30,079
Stronger than the foundations of the earth!

1661
02:44:30,080 --> 02:44:32,679
All shall love me...

1662
02:44:32,680 --> 02:44:36,880
...and despair.

1663
02:44:49,580 --> 02:44:54,179
I pass the test. I will diminish...

1664
02:44:54,180 --> 02:44:56,879
...and go into the West...

1665
02:44:56,880 --> 02:45:02,680
...and remain Galadriel.
- I cannot do this alone.

1666
02:45:04,880 --> 02:45:09,979
You are a ring-bearer, Frodo.
To bear a ring of power...

1667
02:45:09,980 --> 02:45:12,880
...is to be alone.

1668
02:45:14,880 --> 02:45:17,879
This is Nenya, the ring of Adamant.

1669
02:45:17,880 --> 02:45:20,880
And I am its keeper.

1670
02:45:22,680 --> 02:45:27,379
This task was appointed to you.

1671
02:45:27,380 --> 02:45:31,479
And if you do not find a way...

1672
02:45:31,480 --> 02:45:33,879
...no one will.

1673
02:45:33,880 --> 02:45:37,579
Then I know what I must do.

1674
02:45:37,580 --> 02:45:40,280
It's just...

1675
02:45:42,080 --> 02:45:45,780
...I'm afraid to do it.

1676
02:45:47,780 --> 02:45:54,280
Even the smallest person can change
the course of the future.

1677
02:45:58,380 --> 02:46:04,889
Do you know how the orcs first came into being?

1678
02:46:04,890 --> 02:46:09,279
They were elves once.

1679
02:46:09,280 --> 02:46:12,979
Taken by the dark powers...

1680
02:46:12,980 --> 02:46:16,379
...tortured and mutilated.

1681
02:46:16,380 --> 02:46:21,889
A ruined and terrible form of life.

1682
02:46:21,890 --> 02:46:25,190
And now...

1683
02:46:25,290 --> 02:46:27,889
...perfected.

1684
02:46:27,890 --> 02:46:32,390
My fighting Uruk-hai...

1685
02:46:32,990 --> 02:46:35,489
...whom do you serve?

1686
02:46:35,490 --> 02:46:39,390
Saruman!

1687
02:46:58,790 --> 02:47:02,489
Hunt them down. Do not stop until, they are found.

1688
02:47:02,490 --> 02:47:05,589
You do not know pain.
You do not know fear.

1689
02:47:05,590 --> 02:47:09,890
You will taste man-flesh!

1690
02:47:13,590 --> 02:47:17,489
One of the halflings carries
something of great value.

1691
02:47:17,490 --> 02:47:22,990
Bring them to me alive and unspoiled.

1692
02:47:23,590 --> 02:47:26,290
Kill the others.

1693
02:47:37,233 --> 02:47:50,000
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Ai! Laurië lantar lassi súrinen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Ah! Like gold fall the leaves in the wind)</font></i>

1694
02:47:43,990 --> 02:47:50,489
Never before have we clad strangers
in the garb of our own people.

1695
02:47:50,433 --> 02:47:57,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Yéni únótimë...</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Numberless long years...)</font></i>

1696
02:47:50,490 --> 02:47:55,690
May these cloaks help shield
you from unfriendly eyes.

1697
02:48:01,500 --> 02:48:03,399
Lembas.

1698
02:48:03,400 --> 02:48:06,500
Elvish waybread.

1699
02:48:07,400 --> 02:48:11,800
One small bite is enough to fill
the stomach of a grown man.

1700
02:48:16,890 --> 02:48:18,999
How many did you eat?

1701
02:48:19,000 --> 02:48:22,100
Four.

1702
02:48:26,500 --> 02:48:29,299
Every league you travel south,
the danger will increase.

1703
02:48:29,300 --> 02:48:33,599
Mordor orcs now hold the
eastern shore of the Anduin.

1704
02:48:33,600 --> 02:48:36,299
Nor will you find safety on the western bank.

1705
02:48:36,300 --> 02:48:40,399
Strange creatures bearing the mark of the
white hand have been seen on our borders.

1706
02:48:40,400 --> 02:48:46,700
Seldom do orcs journey in the open
under the sun, yet these have done so.

1707
02:48:53,800 --> 02:48:57,500
<font color="#008000">Le aphadar aen.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(You are being followed.)</font>

1708
02:48:58,100 --> 02:49:04,000
By river you have the chance of outrunning
the enemy to the falls of Rauros.

1709
02:49:20,433 --> 02:50:00,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ [Súri]nen yéni únótimë ve rámar aldaron!</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Numberless long years as the wings of trees!)</font></i>

1710
02:49:20,500 --> 02:49:24,999
<i>My gift for you, Legolas, is a bow of the Galadhrim.</i>

1711
02:49:25,000 --> 02:49:29,800
<i>Worthy of the skill of our woodland kin.</i>

1712
02:49:33,900 --> 02:49:36,599
<i>These are the daggers of the Noldorin.</i>

1713
02:49:36,600 --> 02:49:40,699
<i>They have already seen service in war.</i>

1714
02:49:40,700 --> 02:49:43,199
<i>Do not fear, young Peregrin Took.</i>

1715
02:49:43,200 --> 02:49:47,800
<i>You will find your courage.</i>

1716
02:49:48,310 --> 02:49:50,499
<i>And for you, Samwise Gamgee...</i>

1717
02:49:50,500 --> 02:49:53,399
<i>...Elven rope made of hithlain.</i>

1718
02:49:53,400 --> 02:49:56,900
Thank you, my lady.

1719
02:49:57,300 --> 02:50:02,000
Have you run out of those nice, shiny daggers?

1720
02:50:00,600 --> 02:50:17,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Yéni ve lintë yuldar avánier</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The long years have passed like swift draughts)</font></i>

1721
02:50:07,010 --> 02:50:10,299
And what gift would a dwarf ask of the elves?

1722
02:50:10,300 --> 02:50:13,109
Nothing.

1723
02:50:13,110 --> 02:50:17,009
Except to look upon the lady
of the Galadhrim one last time...

1724
02:50:17,010 --> 02:50:23,510
...for she is more fair than all
the jewels beneath the earth.

1725
02:50:18,600 --> 02:50:40,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ mi oromardi lissë-miruvóreva</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(of the sweet mead in lofty halls)</font></i>

1726
02:50:29,210 --> 02:50:31,009
Actually....

1727
02:50:31,010 --> 02:50:33,509
There was one thing.

1728
02:50:33,510 --> 02:50:36,309
No, no, I couIdn't.
It's quite impossible.

1729
02:50:36,310 --> 02:50:40,510
Stupid to ask.

1730
02:50:41,710 --> 02:50:43,909
<i>I have nothing greater to give...</i>

1731
02:50:43,910 --> 02:50:48,409
<i>...than the gift you already bear.</i>

1732
02:50:48,410 --> 02:50:50,909
<font color="#008000">Am meleth dîn...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(For her love...)</font>

1733
02:50:50,910 --> 02:50:57,109
<font color="#008000">I ant e guil Arwen Undómiel pígatha.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(The gift of life of Arwen will dwindle.)</font>

1734
02:50:57,110 --> 02:51:02,009
<font color="#008000">Aníron i e broniatha, ad ae periatham...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(I wish that she endures, even if we separate...)</font>

1735
02:51:02,010 --> 02:51:06,710
<font color="#008000">athar i methid en-amar hen.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(beyond the limits of this world.)</font>

1736
02:51:06,900 --> 02:51:12,690
<font color="#008000">Aníron i e círatha na Valannor.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(I wish that she sails to Valinor.)</font>

1737
02:51:12,910 --> 02:51:16,709
That choice is yet before her.

1738
02:51:16,710 --> 02:51:19,909
You have your own choice to make, Aragorn.

1739
02:51:19,910 --> 02:51:25,909
To rise above the height of all your
fathers since the days of Elendil...

1740
02:51:25,910 --> 02:51:31,610
...or to fall into darkness
with all that is left of your kin.

1741
02:51:37,610 --> 02:51:41,010
<font color="#0080C0">Namárië.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Farewell.)</font>

1742
02:51:43,010 --> 02:51:48,310
<font color="#008000">Nadath nâ i moe cerich.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(There is much you have yet to do.)</font>

1743
02:51:48,510 --> 02:51:57,619
<font color="#008000">Dan, ú-'eveditham, Elessar.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(We shall not meet again, Elessar.)</font>

1744
02:51:57,900 --> 02:52:32,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Namárië! Nai hiruvalyë Valimar!</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Farewell! Maybe thou shalt find Valimar!)</font></i>

1745
02:51:57,920 --> 02:52:01,219
<i>Farewell, Frodo Baggins.</i>

1746
02:52:01,220 --> 02:52:05,519
<i>I give you the light of Earendil...</i>

1747
02:52:05,520 --> 02:52:09,220
<i>...our most beloved star.</i>

1748
02:52:16,920 --> 02:52:21,519
<i>May it be a light for you in dark places...</i>

1749
02:52:21,520 --> 02:52:27,020
<i>... when all other lights go out.</i>

1750
02:52:32,900 --> 02:52:39,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Namá[rië]!</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Farewell!)</font></i>

1751
02:52:34,620 --> 02:52:38,419
I have taken my worst wound at this parting...

1752
02:52:38,420 --> 02:52:43,419
...having looked my last upon that which is fairest.

1753
02:52:43,420 --> 02:52:47,019
Henceforth I will call nothing fair
unless it be her gift to me.

1754
02:52:47,020 --> 02:52:49,219
What was her gift?

1755
02:52:49,220 --> 02:52:54,819
I asked her for one hair from her golden head.

1756
02:52:54,820 --> 02:52:59,120
She gave me three.

1757
02:54:39,930 --> 02:54:44,730
Gollum. He has tracked us since Moria.

1758
02:54:47,130 --> 02:54:50,429
I had hoped we would lose him on the river.

1759
02:54:50,430 --> 02:54:54,429
But he's too clever a waterman.

1760
02:54:54,430 --> 02:54:57,829
And if he alerts the enemy to our whereabouts...

1761
02:54:57,830 --> 02:55:00,229
...it will make the crossing even more dangerous.

1762
02:55:00,230 --> 02:55:02,529
Have some food, Mr. Frodo.

1763
02:55:02,530 --> 02:55:05,929
- No, Sam.
- You haven't eaten anything all day.

1764
02:55:05,930 --> 02:55:09,829
You're not sleeping, neither.
Don't think I haven't noticed.

1765
02:55:09,830 --> 02:55:13,029
- Mr. Frodo
- I'm all right.

1766
02:55:13,030 --> 02:55:14,529
But you're not.

1767
02:55:14,530 --> 02:55:17,229
I'm here to help you.

1768
02:55:17,230 --> 02:55:20,330
I promised Gandalf that I would.

1769
02:55:24,940 --> 02:55:28,940
You can't help me, Sam.

1770
02:55:29,840 --> 02:55:32,940
Not this time.

1771
02:55:34,430 --> 02:55:37,930
Get some sleep.

1772
02:55:42,840 --> 02:55:45,539
Minas Tirith is the safer road.

1773
02:55:45,540 --> 02:55:48,939
You know that.
From there we can regroup.

1774
02:55:48,940 --> 02:55:51,439
Strike out for Mordor from a place of strength.

1775
02:55:51,440 --> 02:55:54,839
There is no strength in Gondor that can avail us.

1776
02:55:54,840 --> 02:55:58,240
You were quick enough to trust the elves.

1777
02:55:58,640 --> 02:56:01,639
Have you so little faith in your own people?

1778
02:56:01,640 --> 02:56:04,839
Yes, there is weakness.
There is frailty.

1779
02:56:04,840 --> 02:56:08,339
But there is courage also,
and honor to be found in men.

1780
02:56:08,340 --> 02:56:10,939
But you will not see that.

1781
02:56:10,940 --> 02:56:12,639
You are afraid!

1782
02:56:12,640 --> 02:56:15,439
All your life, you have hidden in the shadows.

1783
02:56:15,440 --> 02:56:20,240
Scared of who you are, of what you are.

1784
02:56:21,340 --> 02:56:27,040
I will not lead the ring within
a hundred leagues of your city.

1785
02:56:37,540 --> 02:56:40,340
Frodo.

1786
02:56:40,740 --> 02:56:43,640
The Argonath.

1787
02:56:43,970 --> 02:56:59,459
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Et Eärello Endorenna utúlien</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Out of the Great Sea to Middle-earth I come)</font></i>

1788
02:56:45,740 --> 02:56:50,139
Long have I desired to look upon the kings of old.

1789
02:56:50,140 --> 02:56:53,440
My kin.

1790
02:57:00,970 --> 02:57:10,459
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Sinomë maruvan ar Hildinyar</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(In this place I will abide, and my heirs)</font></i>

1791
02:58:11,150 --> 02:58:13,549
We cross the lake at nightfall.

1792
02:58:13,550 --> 02:58:16,249
Hide the boats and continue on foot.

1793
02:58:16,250 --> 02:58:20,149
- We approach Mordor from the North.
- Oh, yes?

1794
02:58:20,150 --> 02:58:24,149
Just a simple matter of finding
our way through Emyn Muil...

1795
02:58:24,150 --> 02:58:27,549
...an impassable labyrinth of razor-sharp rocks.

1796
02:58:27,550 --> 02:58:31,049
And after that, it gets even better.

1797
02:58:31,050 --> 02:58:36,249
Festering, stinking marshland
as far as the eye can see.

1798
02:58:36,250 --> 02:58:39,050
That is our road.

1799
02:58:39,150 --> 02:58:42,549
I suggest you take some rest and
recover your strength, Master Dwarf.

1800
02:58:42,550 --> 02:58:45,650
Recover my...

1801
02:58:47,350 --> 02:58:49,449
- We should Leave now.
- No.

1802
02:58:49,450 --> 02:58:54,049
Orcs patrol the eastern shore.
We must wait for cover of darkness.

1803
02:58:54,050 --> 02:58:57,749
It is not the eastern shore that worries me.

1804
02:58:57,750 --> 02:59:02,249
A shadow and a threat has
been growing in my mind.

1805
02:59:02,250 --> 02:59:07,750
Something draws near.
I can feel it.

1806
02:59:08,450 --> 02:59:13,949
Recover strength?
Pay no heed to that, young hobbit.

1807
02:59:13,950 --> 02:59:17,050
Where's Frodo?

1808
02:59:41,260 --> 02:59:44,459
None of us should wander alone.

1809
02:59:44,460 --> 02:59:46,859
You, least of all.

1810
02:59:46,860 --> 02:59:50,359
So much depends on you.

1811
02:59:50,360 --> 02:59:53,760
Frodo?

1812
02:59:59,460 --> 03:00:02,759
I know why you seek solitude.

1813
03:00:02,760 --> 03:00:06,959
You suffer. I see it day by day.

1814
03:00:06,960 --> 03:00:11,460
You sure you do not suffer needlessly?

1815
03:00:11,660 --> 03:00:14,559
There are other ways, Frodo.

1816
03:00:14,560 --> 03:00:18,559
- Other paths that we might take.
- I know what you would say.

1817
03:00:18,560 --> 03:00:22,559
It would seem like wisdom but
for the warning in my heart.

1818
03:00:22,560 --> 03:00:25,859
Warning...against what?

1819
03:00:25,860 --> 03:00:28,159
We're all afraid, Frodo.

1820
03:00:28,160 --> 03:00:32,059
But to let that fear drive us,
to destroy what hope we have...

1821
03:00:32,060 --> 03:00:37,160
...don't you see that is madness?
- There is no other way.

1822
03:00:37,660 --> 03:00:42,260
I ask only for the strength to defend my people!

1823
03:00:42,560 --> 03:00:45,759
- If you would but lend me the ring.
- No.

1824
03:00:45,760 --> 03:00:50,760
- Why do you recoil? I am no thief.
- You are not yourself.

1825
03:00:51,360 --> 03:00:54,769
What chance do you think you have?

1826
03:00:54,770 --> 03:00:59,659
They will find you.
They will take the ring.

1827
03:00:59,660 --> 03:01:04,760
And you will beg for death before the end!

1828
03:01:05,469 --> 03:01:08,118
<font color="#FF0000">Gûm-ishi...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(In the void...)</font>

1829
03:01:05,570 --> 03:01:07,659
You fool!

1830
03:01:07,760 --> 03:01:11,959
It is not yours, save by unhappy chance!
It could have been mine.

1831
03:01:11,960 --> 03:01:14,900
It should be mine! Give it to me!

1832
03:01:13,734 --> 03:01:14,900
<font color="#FF0000">...ashi...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(...only...)</font>

1833
03:01:14,960 --> 03:01:16,459
- Give it to me!
- No!

1834
03:01:16,460 --> 03:01:19,760
- Give it to me!
- No.

1835
03:01:17,250 --> 03:01:19,069
<font color="#FF0000">...gurum</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(...death)</font>

1836
03:01:25,970 --> 03:01:28,269
I see your mind.

1837
03:01:28,270 --> 03:01:31,369
You will take the ring to Sauron!

1838
03:01:31,370 --> 03:01:33,469
You will betray us!

1839
03:01:33,470 --> 03:01:37,069
You'll go to your death, and the death of us all!

1840
03:01:37,070 --> 03:01:42,070
Curse you!
Curse you and all the halflings!

1841
03:01:47,770 --> 03:01:50,770
Frodo?

1842
03:01:53,570 --> 03:01:56,670
Frodo.

1843
03:01:59,170 --> 03:02:01,369
What have I done?

1844
03:02:01,370 --> 03:02:03,369
Please, Frodo.

1845
03:02:03,370 --> 03:02:07,370
Frodo, I'm sorry!

1846
03:02:33,390 --> 03:02:40,890
<font color="#FF0000">Akha gûm-ishi ashi gurum</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Here in the void, only death)</font>

1847
03:02:54,570 --> 03:02:57,169
Frodo?

1848
03:02:57,170 --> 03:03:00,579
- It has taken Boromir.
- Where is the ring?

1849
03:03:00,580 --> 03:03:02,669
Stay away!

1850
03:03:02,670 --> 03:03:05,770
Frodo!

1851
03:03:06,570 --> 03:03:11,770
- I swore to protect you.
- Can you protect me from yourself?

1852
03:03:12,233 --> 03:03:23,900
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ I tuo i macil a staldaron</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The strength, the weapon, the needs of the valiant)</font></i>

1853
03:03:20,180 --> 03:03:23,980
Would you destroy it?

1854
03:03:24,233 --> 03:03:32,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Marinyë Cor[ma]</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Let the Ring be your weapon)</font></i>

1855
03:03:27,680 --> 03:03:30,980
<i>Aragorn.</i>

1856
03:03:32,233 --> 03:03:45,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ I tuo i macil a lelyat túrenna</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The strength, the weapon, go to victory!)</font></i>

1857
03:03:32,980 --> 03:03:36,680
<i>Aragorn.</i>

1858
03:03:37,180 --> 03:03:40,380
<i>Elessar.</i>

1859
03:03:46,580 --> 03:03:50,579
I would have gone with you to the end.

1860
03:03:50,580 --> 03:03:54,880
Into the very fires of Mordor.

1861
03:03:56,880 --> 03:03:59,480
I know.

1862
03:04:00,380 --> 03:04:07,180
Look after the others. Especially Sam.
He will not understand.

1863
03:04:09,680 --> 03:04:12,780
Go, Frodo!

1864
03:04:14,380 --> 03:04:16,079
Run.

1865
03:04:16,080 --> 03:04:19,180
Run!

1866
03:04:42,280 --> 03:04:45,380
Mr. Frodo!

1867
03:04:53,380 --> 03:04:56,480
Find the halfling!

1868
03:04:56,680 --> 03:05:00,580
Find the halfling!

1869
03:05:02,780 --> 03:05:05,880
Elendil!

1870
03:05:10,890 --> 03:05:13,890
Aragorn, go!

1871
03:05:34,090 --> 03:05:35,989
Frodo!

1872
03:05:35,990 --> 03:05:38,289
Hide here. Quick!

1873
03:05:38,290 --> 03:05:41,190
Come on!

1874
03:05:42,190 --> 03:05:45,690
What's he doing?

1875
03:05:48,390 --> 03:05:51,890
He's leaving.

1876
03:05:55,290 --> 03:05:59,590
- No!
- Pippin!

1877
03:06:03,090 --> 03:06:05,989
Run, Frodo. Go!

1878
03:06:05,990 --> 03:06:09,489
- Hey! Hey, you!
- Over here!

1879
03:06:09,490 --> 03:06:12,490
- Over here!
- This way!

1880
03:06:21,990 --> 03:06:25,690
- It's working!
- I know it's working! Run!

1881
03:06:40,000 --> 03:06:55,000
<i><font color="#FF0000">♫ Ash Burz-Durbagu burzum-ishi</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(One for the Dark Lord on his dark throne)</font></i>

1882
03:07:19,600 --> 03:07:24,000
- The horn of Gondor.
- Boromir.

1883
03:07:58,970 --> 03:08:16,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ú-velin i vegil an aegas</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(I do not love the bright sword for its sharpness)</font></i>

1884
03:08:05,800 --> 03:08:08,300
Run!

1885
03:08:16,970 --> 03:08:38,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Egor i... bilin a linn[as]</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Nor the... arrow for its swiftness)</font></i>

1886
03:08:48,233 --> 03:09:00,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ I alda helda, i ehtelë lína</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The tree is bare, the fountain still)</font></i>

1887
03:09:01,233 --> 03:09:16,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Manna lelyalye Voromírë?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Whither goest thou Boromir?)</font></i>

1888
03:09:18,233 --> 03:09:35,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Cánalya desse sí mas[së]</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(We heard your call but cannot find you)</font></i>

1889
03:11:38,520 --> 03:11:41,520
No.

1890
03:11:44,120 --> 03:11:47,319
- They took the little ones.
- Hold still.

1891
03:11:47,320 --> 03:11:50,820
Frodo. Where is Frodo?

1892
03:11:51,320 --> 03:11:53,419
I let Frodo go.

1893
03:11:53,420 --> 03:11:57,019
Then you did what I could not.

1894
03:11:57,020 --> 03:12:00,819
I tried to take the ring from him.

1895
03:12:00,820 --> 03:12:05,319
- The ring is beyond our reach now.
- Forgive me.

1896
03:12:05,320 --> 03:12:07,819
I did not see it.

1897
03:12:07,820 --> 03:12:11,519
- I have failed you all.
- No, Boromir.

1898
03:12:11,520 --> 03:12:14,319
You fought bravely.

1899
03:12:14,320 --> 03:12:17,619
You have kept your honor.

1900
03:12:17,620 --> 03:12:19,819
Leave it.

1901
03:12:19,820 --> 03:12:23,129
It is over.

1902
03:12:23,130 --> 03:12:28,819
The world of men will fall and
all will come to darkness...

1903
03:12:28,820 --> 03:12:33,120
...and my city to ruin.

1904
03:12:35,830 --> 03:12:38,729
I do not know what strength is in my blood...

1905
03:12:38,730 --> 03:12:43,729
...but I swear to you, I will
not let the white city fall...

1906
03:12:43,730 --> 03:12:47,129
...nor our people fail.

1907
03:12:47,130 --> 03:12:50,030
Our people.

1908
03:12:52,430 --> 03:12:55,930
Our people.

1909
03:13:16,230 --> 03:13:20,630
I would have followed you, my brother.

1910
03:13:20,830 --> 03:13:24,230
My captain.

1911
03:13:25,530 --> 03:13:28,830
My king.

1912
03:13:28,970 --> 03:13:50,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ú-velin i ve[gil]</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(I do not love the bright sword)</font></i>

1913
03:13:47,030 --> 03:13:49,729
Be at peace...

1914
03:13:49,730 --> 03:13:53,030
...son of Gondor.

1915
03:14:08,030 --> 03:14:11,929
They will look for his coming from the white tower.

1916
03:14:11,930 --> 03:14:16,330
But he will not return.

1917
03:14:38,240 --> 03:14:41,640
Frodo!

1918
03:14:59,640 --> 03:15:04,139
I wish the ring had never come to me.

1919
03:15:04,140 --> 03:15:08,440
I wish none of this had happened.

1920
03:15:10,140 --> 03:15:13,139
So do all who live to see such times...

1921
03:15:13,140 --> 03:15:16,839
...but that is not for them to decide.

1922
03:15:16,840 --> 03:15:19,639
All you have to decide...

1923
03:15:19,640 --> 03:15:25,740
...is what to do with the time that is given to you.

1924
03:15:53,140 --> 03:15:55,939
Frodo, no!

1925
03:15:55,940 --> 03:15:57,849
Frodo!

1926
03:15:57,850 --> 03:16:01,950
- Mr. Frodo!
- No, Sam.

1927
03:16:04,140 --> 03:16:06,639
Go back, Sam!

1928
03:16:06,640 --> 03:16:10,339
- I'm going to Mordor alone.
- Of course you are.

1929
03:16:10,340 --> 03:16:13,739
And I'm coming with you!

1930
03:16:13,740 --> 03:16:17,540
You can't swim!

1931
03:16:19,840 --> 03:16:23,040
Sam!

1932
03:16:27,150 --> 03:16:30,050
Sam!

1933
03:17:09,450 --> 03:17:12,549
I made a promise, Mr. Frodo.

1934
03:17:12,550 --> 03:17:17,949
A promise:
"Don't you leave him, Samwise Gamgee."

1935
03:17:17,950 --> 03:17:20,849
And I don't mean to.

1936
03:17:20,850 --> 03:17:24,450
I don't mean to.

1937
03:17:24,750 --> 03:17:27,950
Oh Sam.

1938
03:17:41,450 --> 03:17:44,550
Come on.

1939
03:18:11,450 --> 03:18:17,350
Hurry! Frodo and Sam have
reached the eastern shore.

1940
03:18:30,960 --> 03:18:37,360
- You mean not to follow them.
- Frodo's fate is no longer in our hands.

1941
03:18:39,360 --> 03:18:45,560
Then it has all been in vain.
The fellowship has failed.

1942
03:18:56,060 --> 03:19:00,660
Not if we hold true to each other.

1943
03:19:00,660 --> 03:19:06,059
We will not abandon Merry and
Pippin to torment and death.

1944
03:19:06,060 --> 03:19:12,660
Not while we have strength left.
Leave all that can be spared behind.

1945
03:19:12,660 --> 03:19:14,859
We travel light.

1946
03:19:14,860 --> 03:19:18,260
Let us hunt some orc.

1947
03:19:19,760 --> 03:19:23,260
Yes!

1948
03:19:40,760 --> 03:19:42,859
Mordor.

1949
03:19:42,860 --> 03:19:47,159
I hope the others find a safer road.

1950
03:19:47,160 --> 03:19:50,769
Strider will look after them.

1951
03:19:50,770 --> 03:19:54,459
I don't suppose we'll ever see them again.

1952
03:19:54,460 --> 03:19:56,969
We may yet, Mr. Frodo.

1953
03:19:56,970 --> 03:19:59,970
We may.

1954
03:20:00,670 --> 03:20:03,270
Sam...

1955
03:20:05,370 --> 03:20:09,370
...I'm glad you are with me.

1956
03:21:14,808 --> 03:21:20,365
<i>♫ Shines down upon you</i>

1957
03:21:21,968 --> 03:21:28,032
<i>♫ May it be when darkness falls</i>

1958
03:21:28,056 --> 03:21:34,625
<i>♫ Your heart will be true</i>

1959
03:21:35,212 --> 03:21:41,387
<i>♫ You walk a lonely road</i>

1960
03:21:41,411 --> 03:21:50,922
<i>♫ Oh! How far you are from home</i>

1961
03:21:52,002 --> 03:22:03,585
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Mornie utúlië</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Darkness has come)</font></i>

1962
03:22:03,609 --> 03:22:15,526
<i>♫ Believe and you will find your way</i>

1963
03:22:15,550 --> 03:22:27,968
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Mornie alantië</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Darkness has fallen)</font></i>

1964
03:22:27,992 --> 03:22:39,402
<i>♫ A promise lives within you now</i>

1965
03:22:42,558 --> 03:22:48,609
<i>♫ May it be the shadow's call</i>

1966
03:22:48,633 --> 03:22:54,086
<i>♫ Will fly away</i>

1967
03:22:55,632 --> 03:23:01,537
<i>♫ May it be you journey on</i>

1968
03:23:01,561 --> 03:23:06,927
<i>♫ To light the day</i>

1969
03:23:08,066 --> 03:23:14,415
<i>♫ When the night is overcome</i>

1970
03:23:14,439 --> 03:23:23,212
<i>♫ You may rise to find the sun</i>

1971
03:23:23,402 --> 03:23:36,000
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Mornie utúlië</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Darkness has come)</font></i>

1972
03:23:36,173 --> 03:23:47,753
<i>♫ Believe and you will find your way</i>

1973
03:23:47,778 --> 03:23:59,532
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Mornie alantië</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Darkness has fallen)</font></i>

1974
03:23:59,556 --> 03:24:11,965
<i>♫ A promise lives within you now</i>

1975
03:24:11,991 --> 03:24:24,076
<i>♫ A promise lives within you...</i>

1976
03:24:24,100 --> 03:24:31,400
<i>♫ ...now</i>

1977
03:25:08,430 --> 03:25:14,835
<i>♫ When the cold of winter comes</i>

1978
03:25:14,859 --> 03:25:21,206
<i>♫ Starless night will cover day</i>

1979
03:25:21,230 --> 03:25:27,396
<i>♫ In the veiling of the sun</i>

1980
03:25:27,420 --> 03:25:34,353
<i>♫ We will walk in bitter rain</i>

1981
03:25:34,640 --> 03:25:39,676
<i>♫ But in dreams</i>

1982
03:25:39,700 --> 03:25:46,670
<i>♫ I can hear your name</i>

1983
03:25:46,694 --> 03:25:52,592
<i>♫ And in dreams</i>

1984
03:25:52,616 --> 03:26:03,703
<i>♫ We will meet again</i>

